=89=E2=8B=85=E2=80=89(22=E2=8B=851001 =E2=88=92 1) =3D 198585576189</span> =
would be an odd perfect number if only <span class=3D"texhtml">22021 (=3D 1=
9<sup>2</sup> =E2=8B=85 61)</span> were a prime number.  The odd numbers wi=
th this property (they would be perfect if one of their composite factors w=
ere prime) are the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Descartes_numbe=
r" title=3D"Descartes number">Descartes numbers</a>. Many of the properties=
 proven about odd perfect numbers also apply to Descartes numbers, and Pace=
